{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":52117,"duration_api_ms":52081,"num_turns":10,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"4f1d4934-af02-494f-9bae-827580fae330","total_cost_usd":0.33019550000000003,"usage":{"input_tokens":9,"cache_creation_input_tokens":25662,"cache_read_input_tokens":243626,"output_tokens":1918,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":25662,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":9,"outputTokens":1918,"cacheReadInputTokens":243626,"cacheCreationInputTokens":25662,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.33019550000000003,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Both amendments identify genuine correctness defects in the task run lineage tracking code, confirmed by reading the source. Amendment fr-12-5e41079a correctly identifies that legacy running rows are silently adopted and backfilled by new named runs, destroying the earlier attempt's identity. Amendment fr-12-eaae97d7 correctly identifies that the started_at timestamp fallback in same_attempt is insufficiently unique, allowing distinct legacy retries to be collapsed into a single visible entry by collapse_task_run_attempts.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-12-5e41079a","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified in code: find_matching_running_task_run (model.rs:437-441) falls back to any sole legacy entry (run_id == None) when the new start carries a run_id. backfill_running_entry (fs.rs:2687-2690) then stamps the new run_id onto that old row. This is correct for idempotent replay of the same in-flight run, but for a genuinely new retry after upgrade, the old open attempt is silently rewritten into the new run — the earlier attempt vanishes from lineage. This is a real audit/retry-history correctness defect."},{"amendment_id":"fr-12-eaae97d7","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified in code: same_attempt (model.rs:307-310) uses started_at equality as the identity fallback whenever either entry lacks run_id. can_collapse_attempt_entries (model.rs:486-490) further allows collapsing terminal entries with the same outcome via this same_attempt check. find_runs_for_bead (fs.rs:3133) applies collapse_task_run_attempts to the full entry list. Since run_id is intentionally optional for backward compatibility, two distinct legacy retries with coincident (or truncated-to-same-second) timestamps and the same terminal outcome will be merged into one visible entry. This breaks the requirement that multiple retries remain independently visible."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"c924aafa-d0af-49fa-8184-c6303869f1b8"}
